工作描述
Executive Assistant – SCM
       Key Responsibilities:
Management of complex calendar and scheduling to support senior leader
Managing domestic and international travel
Manage expense report coordination and submission
Organize, execute and assist with team activities (staff meetings, All-Hands meetings and team social events)
Work closely with the leadership team and other Executive Assistants to provide support to the organization
 
       Qualifications:
Bachelor’s Degree
Experience providing support assistance
Written and Spoken English, CET-6
Fluent Chinese
Strong verbal and written communication skills
Strong organizational and interpersonal skills
Excellent Microsoft Outlook, Word and Excel management skills
 
       Preferred:
Written and Spoken Korean
Project management or back-office work experience
Strong analytical skills
1-3 years prior executive assistant experience
Ability to prioritize and handle multiple assignments at any given time
Experience in Retail, E-Commerce or Supply Chain